description: Ba₂ZnN₂ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded to five equivalent N(1)³⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing BaN₅ square pyramids. There is one shorter (2.651 Å) and four longer (2.990 Å) Ba(1)-N(1) bond lengths. Zn(1)²⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent N(1)³⁻ atoms. Both Zn(1)-N(1) bond lengths are 1.848 Å. N(1)³⁻ is bonded to five equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and one Zn(1)²⁺ atom to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing NBa₅Zn octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 0-7°.

BaO₂ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. Ba(1) is bonded in a distorted q4 geometry to ten equivalent O(1) atoms. There are two shorter (2.738 Å) and eight longer (2.835 Å) Ba(1)-O(1) bond lengths. O(1) is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to five equivalent Ba(1) and one O(1) atom. The O(1)-O(1) bond length is 1.503 Å.

ZrGeO₄ is Zircon-like structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal I4₁/a space group. Zr(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to eight equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. There are four shorter (2.165 Å) and four longer (2.304 Å) Zr(1)-O(1) bond lengths. Ge(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a tetrahedral geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All Ge(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.794 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal planar geometry to two equivalent Zr(1)⁴⁺ and one Ge(1)⁴⁺ atom.

KCaBr₃ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/m space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Br(2)¹⁻ and six equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (3.298 Å) and one longer (3.299 Å) K(1)-Br(2) bond length. There are a spread of K(1)-Br(1) bond distances ranging from 3.500-3.688 Å. Ca(1)²⁺ is bonded to two equivalent Br(2)¹⁻ and four equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing CaBr₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 42°. Both Ca(1)-Br(2) bond lengths are 2.903 Å. All Ca(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.942 Å. There are two inequivalent Br¹⁻ sites. In the first Br¹⁻ site, Br(2)¹⁻ is bonded to two equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ atoms to form distorted corner-sharing BrK₂Ca₂ tetrahedra. In the second Br¹⁻ site, Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to three equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ atoms.

Rb₂Pd₃S₄ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Fmmm space group. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to eight equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. There are a spread of Rb(1)-S(1) bond distances ranging from 3.610-3.718 Å. There are two inequivalent Pd²⁺ sites. In the first Pd²⁺ site, Pd(1)²⁺ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. All Pd(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.377 Å. In the second Pd²⁺ site, Pd(2)²⁺ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. All Pd(2)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.368 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺, one Pd(2)²⁺, and two equivalent Pd(1)²⁺ atoms.

CsMgI₃ crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃/mmc space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded to twelve equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms to form CsI₁₂ cuboctahedra that share corners with six equivalent Cs(1)I₁₂ cuboctahedra, corners with six equivalent Mg(1)I₆ octahedra, faces with eight equivalent Cs(1)I₁₂ cuboctahedra, and faces with six equivalent Mg(1)I₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 18°. There are six shorter (4.189 Å) and six longer (4.344 Å) Cs(1)-I(1) bond lengths. Mg(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms to form MgI₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Cs(1)I₁₂ cuboctahedra, faces with six equivalent Cs(1)I₁₂ cuboctahedra, and faces with two equivalent Mg(1)I₆ octahedra. All Mg(1)-I(1) bond lengths are 2.946 Å. I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Mg(1)²⁺ atoms.

NaRhO₂ is Caswellsilverite structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. Na(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form NaO₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Rh(1)O₆ octahedra, edges with six equivalent Na(1)O₆ octahedra, and edges with six equivalent Rh(1)O₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 11°. All Na(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.405 Å. Rh(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form RhO₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Na(1)O₆ octahedra, edges with six equivalent Na(1)O₆ octahedra, and edges with six equivalent Rh(1)O₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 11°. All Rh(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.100 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Na(1)¹⁺ and three equivalent Rh(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing ONa₃Rh₃ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted.

K₄HgAs₂ crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. There are two inequivalent K¹⁺ sites. In the first K¹⁺ site, K(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing KAs₄ tetrahedra. There is one shorter (3.351 Å) and three longer (3.507 Å) K(1)-As(1) bond lengths. In the second K¹⁺ site, K(2)¹⁺ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms. All K(2)-As(1) bond lengths are 3.489 Å. Hg(1)²⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms. Both Hg(1)-As(1) bond lengths are 2.527 Å. As(1)³⁻ is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to three equivalent K(2)¹⁺, four equivalent K(1)¹⁺, and one Hg(1)²⁺ atom.

InS is Hittorf-derived structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pnnm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two InS sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. In(1)²⁺ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (2.546 Å) and two longer (2.585 Å) In(1)-S(1) bond lengths. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent In(1)²⁺ atoms.

Cs₂NaAlH₆ is (Cubic) Perovskite-derived structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded to twelve equivalent H(1)¹⁻ atoms to form CsH₁₂ cuboctahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Cs(1)H₁₂ cuboctahedra, faces with six equivalent Cs(1)H₁₂ cuboctahedra, faces with four equivalent Na(1)H₆ octahedra, and faces with four equivalent Al(1)H₆ octahedra. All Cs(1)-H(1) bond lengths are 3.070 Å. Na(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent H(1)¹⁻ atoms to form NaH₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Al(1)H₆ octahedra and faces with eight equivalent Cs(1)H₁₂ cuboctahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Na(1)-H(1) bond lengths are 2.512 Å. Al(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent H(1)¹⁻ atoms to form AlH₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Na(1)H₆ octahedra and faces with eight equivalent Cs(1)H₁₂ cuboctahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Al(1)-H(1) bond lengths are 1.801 Å. H(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺, one Na(1)¹⁺, and one Al(1)³⁺ atom.

GeO₂ is Rutile structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal P4₂/mnm space group. Ge(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing GeO₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 50°. There are four shorter (1.900 Å) and two longer (1.947 Å) Ge(1)-O(1) bond lengths. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent Ge(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

CsSbO₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/c space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. There are a spread of Cs(1)-O(1) bond distances ranging from 3.028-3.508 Å. Sb(1)³⁺ is bonded in a distorted see-saw-like geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. There are two shorter (1.998 Å) and two longer (2.204 Å) Sb(1)-O(1) bond lengths. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Sb(1)³⁺ atoms.

LiAsS₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic Cc space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to two equivalent S(2)²⁻ and four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing LiS₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 10-12°. There is one shorter (2.657 Å) and one longer (2.899 Å) Li(1)-S(2) bond length. There are a spread of Li(1)-S(1) bond distances ranging from 2.685-2.759 Å. As(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to one S(1)²⁻ and two equivalent S(2)²⁻ atoms. The As(1)-S(1) bond length is 2.207 Å. There is one shorter (2.367 Å) and one longer (2.370 Å) As(1)-S(2) bond length. There are two inequivalent S²⁻ sites. In the first S²⁻ site, S(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ and one As(1)³⁺ atom to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing SLi₄As square pyramids. In the second S²⁻ site, S(2)²⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent As(1)³⁺ atoms.

Ca₂NBr is Caswellsilverite structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. Ca(1)²⁺ is bonded to three equivalent N(1)³⁻ and three equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing CaBr₃N₃ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Ca(1)-N(1) bond lengths are 2.473 Å. All Ca(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 3.108 Å. N(1)³⁻ is bonded to six equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ atoms to form edge-sharing NCa₆ octahedra. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ atoms.

CsSbF₆ crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3 space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded to twelve equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form CsF₁₂ cuboctahedra that share corners with six equivalent Sb(1)F₆ octahedra, edges with six equivalent Cs(1)F₁₂ cuboctahedra, and faces with two equivalent Sb(1)F₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 36°. There are six shorter (3.198 Å) and six longer (3.428 Å) Cs(1)-F(1) bond lengths. Sb(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to six equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form SbF₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Cs(1)F₁₂ cuboctahedra and faces with two equivalent Cs(1)F₁₂ cuboctahedra. All Sb(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 1.923 Å. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to two equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ and one Sb(1)⁵⁺ atom.

CaB₂C₂ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mcm space group. Ca(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to eight equivalent C(1)⁴⁻ atoms. All Ca(1)-C(1) bond lengths are 2.744 Å. B(1)³⁺ is bonded in a distorted trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent C(1)⁴⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (1.531 Å) and two longer (1.604 Å) B(1)-C(1) bond lengths. C(1)⁴⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ and three equivalent B(1)³⁺ atoms.

K₂CsSb is Heusler structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 14-coordinate geometry to eight equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and six equivalent Sb(1)³⁻ atoms. All Cs(1)-K(1) bond lengths are 3.793 Å. All Cs(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths are 4.379 Å. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a distorted body-centered cubic geometry to four equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ and four equivalent Sb(1)³⁻ atoms. All K(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths are 3.793 Å. Sb(1)³⁻ is bonded in a distorted body-centered cubic geometry to six equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ and eight equivalent K(1)¹⁺ atoms.

MoSe₂ is Molybdenite structured and crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃/mmc space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two MoSe₂ sheets oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Mo(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form distorted edge-sharing MoSe₆ pentagonal pyramids. All Mo(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.547 Å. Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Mo(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

HgBaO₂ crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing BaO₆ octahedra. All Ba(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.741 Å. Hg(1)²⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Both Hg(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.001 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and one Hg(1)²⁺ atom to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing OBa₃Hg tetrahedra.

KLi₂As crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmmn space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing KAs₄ tetrahedra. There are two shorter (3.566 Å) and two longer (3.685 Å) K(1)-As(1) bond lengths. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (2.618 Å) and two longer (2.629 Å) Li(1)-As(1) bond lengths. As(1)³⁻ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to four equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and six equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ atoms.

CdGa₂S₄ crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅4 space group. Cd(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form CdS₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Ga(1)S₄ tetrahedra and corners with four equivalent Ga(2)S₄ tetrahedra. All Cd(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.570 Å. There are two inequivalent Ga³⁺ sites. In the first Ga³⁺ site, Ga(1)³⁺ is bonded to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form GaS₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Cd(1)S₄ tetrahedra and corners with four equivalent Ga(2)S₄ tetrahedra. All Ga(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.309 Å. In the second Ga³⁺ site, Ga(2)³⁺ is bonded to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form GaS₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Cd(1)S₄ tetrahedra and corners with four equivalent Ga(1)S₄ tetrahedra. All Ga(2)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.313 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to one Cd(1)²⁺, one Ga(1)³⁺, and one Ga(2)³⁺ atom.

RbF is Halite, Rock Salt structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing RbF₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Rb(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.869 Å. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded to six equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing FRb₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted.

CsCu₃O₂ crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing CsO₆ octahedra. All Cs(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 3.446 Å. Cu(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Both Cu(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.858 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ and three equivalent Cu(1)¹⁺ atoms.

Ag₂GeS₃ is Enargite-like structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmc2₁ space group. Ag(1)¹⁺ is bonded to one S(1)²⁻ and three equivalent S(2)²⁻ atoms to form AgS₄ tetrahedra that share corners with five equivalent Ge(1)S₄ tetrahedra and corners with seven equivalent Ag(1)S₄ tetrahedra. The Ag(1)-S(1) bond length is 2.610 Å. There are a spread of Ag(1)-S(2) bond distances ranging from 2.547-2.601 Å. Ge(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to two equivalent S(1)²⁻ and two equivalent S(2)²⁻ atoms to form GeS₄ tetrahedra that share corners with two equivalent Ge(1)S₄ tetrahedra and corners with ten equivalent Ag(1)S₄ tetrahedra. There is one shorter (2.321 Å) and one longer (2.387 Å) Ge(1)-S(1) bond length. Both Ge(1)-S(2) bond lengths are 2.205 Å. There are two inequivalent S²⁻ sites. In the first S²⁻ site, S(1)²⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Ag(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Ge(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form SAg₂Ge₂ tetrahedra that share corners with two equivalent S(1)Ag₂Ge₂ tetrahedra and corners with ten equivalent S(2)Ag₃Ge tetrahedra. In the second S²⁻ site, S(2)²⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Ag(1)¹⁺ and one Ge(1)⁴⁺ atom to form SAg₃Ge tetrahedra that share corners with five equivalent S(1)Ag₂Ge₂ tetrahedra and corners with seven equivalent S(2)Ag₃Ge tetrahedra.

YZnAsO is Parent of FeAs superconductors structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. Y(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent As(1)³⁻ and four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All Y(1)-As(1) bond lengths are 3.315 Å. All Y(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.267 Å. Zn(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing ZnAs₄ tetrahedra. All Zn(1)-As(1) bond lengths are 2.572 Å. As(1)³⁻ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Y(1)³⁺ and four equivalent Zn(1)²⁺ atoms. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Y(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing OY₄ tetrahedra.

BAsO₄ crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅4 space group. B(1)³⁺ is bonded to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form BO₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent As(1)O₄ tetrahedra. All B(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.481 Å. As(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form AsO₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent B(1)O₄ tetrahedra. All As(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.721 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a bent 120 degrees geometry to one B(1)³⁺ and one As(1)⁵⁺ atom.

Na₄OI₂ is (La,Ba)CuO4 structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. There are two inequivalent Na¹⁺ sites. In the first Na¹⁺ site, Na(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to one O(1)²⁻ and five equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms. The Na(1)-O(1) bond length is 2.301 Å. There is one shorter (3.288 Å) and four longer (3.333 Å) Na(1)-I(1) bond lengths. In the second Na¹⁺ site, Na(2)¹⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ and four equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms. Both Na(2)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.354 Å. All Na(2)-I(1) bond lengths are 3.412 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Na(1)¹⁺ and four equivalent Na(2)¹⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing ONa₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Na(2)¹⁺ and five equivalent Na(1)¹⁺ atoms.

HK₁ is Halite, Rock Salt structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent H(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing KH₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All K(1)-H(1) bond lengths are 2.848 Å. H(1)¹⁻ is bonded to six equivalent K(1)¹⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing HK₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted.

CsBr is Halite, Rock Salt structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing CsBr₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Cs(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 3.701 Å. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded to six equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing BrCs₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted.

Cs₂TlGaF₆ crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded to twelve equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form distorted CsF₁₂ cuboctahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Cs(1)F₁₂ cuboctahedra, faces with six equivalent Cs(1)F₁₂ cuboctahedra, faces with four equivalent Tl(1)F₆ octahedra, and faces with four equivalent Ga(1)F₆ octahedra. All Cs(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 3.322 Å. Tl(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form TlF₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Ga(1)F₆ octahedra and faces with eight equivalent Cs(1)F₁₂ cuboctahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Tl(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.725 Å. Ga(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form GaF₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Tl(1)F₆ octahedra and faces with eight equivalent Cs(1)F₁₂ cuboctahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Ga(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 1.941 Å. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 1-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺, one Tl(1)¹⁺, and one Ga(1)³⁺ atom.

ScPtSb is half-Heusler structured and crystallizes in the cubic F̅43m space group. Sc(1)³⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Pt(1)²⁻ and six equivalent Sb(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted corner and face-sharing ScSb₆Pt₄ tetrahedra. All Sc(1)-Pt(1) bond lengths are 2.768 Å. All Sc(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths are 3.196 Å. Pt(1)²⁻ is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to four equivalent Sc(1)³⁺ and four equivalent Sb(1)¹⁻ atoms. All Pt(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths are 2.768 Å. Sb(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 10-coordinate geometry to six equivalent Sc(1)³⁺ and four equivalent Pt(1)²⁻ atoms.

AlSb is Zincblende, Sphalerite structured and crystallizes in the cubic F̅43m space group. Al(1)³⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Sb(1)³⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing AlSb₄ tetrahedra. All Al(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths are 2.699 Å. Sb(1)³⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Al(1)³⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing SbAl₄ tetrahedra.

NaCuO₂ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmcm space group. Na(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. There are two shorter (2.374 Å) and four longer (2.508 Å) Na(1)-O(1) bond lengths. Cu(1)³⁺ is bonded in a rectangular see-saw-like geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. There are two shorter (1.846 Å) and two longer (1.847 Å) Cu(1)-O(1) bond lengths. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Na(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Cu(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge, corner, and face-sharing ONa₃Cu₂ trigonal bipyramids.

Y₂Cl₃ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Y₂Cl₃ sheet oriented in the (2, 0, -1) direction. There are two inequivalent Y sites. In the first Y site, Y(1) is bonded in a pentagonal planar geometry to one Cl(1), one Cl(2), and three equivalent Cl(3) atoms. The Y(1)-Cl(1) bond length is 2.723 Å. The Y(1)-Cl(2) bond length is 2.740 Å. There is one shorter (2.802 Å) and two longer (2.837 Å) Y(1)-Cl(3) bond lengths. In the second Y site, Y(2) is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Cl(1) and two equivalent Cl(2) atoms. Both Y(2)-Cl(1) bond lengths are 2.755 Å. Both Y(2)-Cl(2) bond lengths are 2.786 Å. There are three inequivalent Cl sites. In the first Cl site, Cl(1) is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to one Y(1) and two equivalent Y(2) atoms. In the second Cl site, Cl(2) is bonded in a distorted rectangular see-saw-like geometry to one Y(1) and two equivalent Y(2) atoms. In the third Cl site, Cl(3) is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent Y(1) atoms.

Na₂TlSb is Heusler structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Na(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to four equivalent Tl(1)¹⁺ and four equivalent Sb(1)³⁻ atoms. All Na(1)-Tl(1) bond lengths are 3.299 Å. All Na(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths are 3.299 Å. Tl(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to eight equivalent Na(1)¹⁺ atoms. Both Cd(2)-As(1) bond lengths are 2.598 Å. The Cd(2)-I(1) bond length is 3.087 Å. The Cd(2)-I(2) bond length is 3.016 Å. In the third Cd²⁺ site, Cd(3)²⁺ is bonded to one As(1)³⁻, one I(3)¹⁻, and two equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms to form CdAsI₃ tetrahedra that share corners with two equivalent Cd(1)AsI₃ tetrahedra, corners with two equivalent Cd(3)AsI₃ tetrahedra, and corners with four equivalent Cd(2)As₂I₂ tetrahedra. The Cd(3)-As(1) bond length is 2.594 Å. The Cd(3)-I(3) bond length is 2.861 Å. Both Cd(3)-I(1) bond lengths are 2.956 Å. As(1)³⁻ is bonded to one Cd(1)²⁺, one Cd(3)²⁺, and two equivalent Cd(2)²⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing AsCd₄ tetrahedra. There are three inequivalent I¹⁻ sites. In the first I¹⁻ site, I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to one Cd(2)²⁺ and two equivalent Cd(3)²⁺ atoms. In the second I¹⁻ site, I(2)¹⁻ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to one Cd(2)²⁺ and two equivalent Cd(1)²⁺ atoms. In the third I¹⁻ site, I(3)¹⁻ is bonded in a water-like geometry to one Cd(1)²⁺ and one Cd(3)²⁺ atom.

Hg(AsO₃)₂ crystallizes in the trigonal P̅31m space group. Hg(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form HgO₆ octahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent As(1)O₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 53°. All Hg(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.414 Å. As(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form AsO₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Hg(1)O₆ octahedra and edges with three equivalent As(1)O₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 53°. All As(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.869 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal planar geometry to one Hg(1)²⁺ and two equivalent As(1)⁵⁺ atoms.

ZnPbF₆ crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3 space group. Zn(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form ZnF₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Pb(1)F₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 39°. All Zn(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.051 Å. Pb(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form PbF₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Zn(1)F₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 39°. All Pb(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.114 Å. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a bent 150 degrees geometry to one Zn(1)²⁺ and one Pb(1)⁴⁺ atom.

Ag₂HgI₄ crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅4 space group. There are two inequivalent Ag¹⁺ sites. In the first Ag¹⁺ site, Ag(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms to form AgI₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Ag(2)I₄ tetrahedra and corners with four equivalent Hg(1)I₄ tetrahedra. All Ag(1)-I(1) bond lengths are 2.874 Å. In the second Ag¹⁺ site, Ag(2)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms to form AgI₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Ag(1)I₄ tetrahedra and corners with four equivalent Hg(1)I₄ tetrahedra. All Ag(2)-I(1) bond lengths are 2.875 Å. Hg(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms to form HgI₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Ag(1)I₄ tetrahedra and corners with four equivalent Ag(2)I₄ tetrahedra. All Hg(1)-I(1) bond lengths are 2.878 Å. I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to one Ag(1)¹⁺, one Ag(2)¹⁺, and one Hg(1)²⁺ atom.

CaCO₃ is Calcite structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3c space group. Ca(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing CaO₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 62°. All Ca(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.389 Å. C(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All C(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.299 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to two equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ and one C(1)⁴⁺ atom.

CsF is Tetraauricupride structured and crystallizes in the cubic Pm̅3m space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to eight equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms. All Cs(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 3.206 Å. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to eight equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ atoms.

LiBeSb crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃mc space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Sb(1)³⁻ atoms to form LiSb₆ octahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Li(1)Sb₆ octahedra, corners with nine equivalent Be(1)Sb₄ tetrahedra, edges with six equivalent Li(1)Sb₆ octahedra, edges with three equivalent Be(1)Sb₄ tetrahedra, faces with two equivalent Li(1)Sb₆ octahedra, and faces with three equivalent Be(1)Sb₄ tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 48°. There are three shorter (2.898 Å) and three longer (2.995 Å) Li(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths. Be(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Sb(1)³⁻ atoms to form BeSb₄ tetrahedra that share corners with nine equivalent Li(1)Sb₆ octahedra, corners with twelve equivalent Be(1)Sb₄ tetrahedra, edges with three equivalent Li(1)Sb₆ octahedra, and faces with three equivalent Li(1)Sb₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 16-55°. There are three shorter (2.536 Å) and one longer (2.597 Å) Be(1)-Sb(1) bond length. Sb(1)³⁻ is bonded in a 10-coordinate geometry to six equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ and four equivalent Be(1)²⁺ atoms.

ScAlOC crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. There are two inequivalent Sc³⁺ sites. In the first Sc³⁺ site, Sc(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent C(1)⁴⁻ atoms to form ScC₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Al(1)C₃O tetrahedra, edges with six equivalent Sc(1)C₆ octahedra, and edges with six equivalent Al(1)C₃O tetrahedra. All Sc(1)-C(1) bond lengths are 2.395 Å. In the second Sc³⁺ site, Sc(2)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form ScO₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Al(1)C₃O tetrahedra and edges with six equivalent Sc(2)O₆ octahedra. All Sc(2)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.151 Å. Al(1)³⁺ is bonded to three equivalent C(1)⁴⁻ and one O(1)²⁻ atom to form AlC₃O tetrahedra that share corners with three equivalent Sc(1)C₆ octahedra, corners with three equivalent Sc(2)O₆ octahedra, corners with six equivalent Al(1)C₃O tetrahedra, and edges with three equivalent Sc(1)C₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 17-62°. All Al(1)-C(1) bond lengths are 2.030 Å. The Al(1)-O(1) bond length is 1.857 Å. C(1)⁴⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Sc(1)³⁺ and three equivalent Al(1)³⁺ atoms to form distorted CSc₃Al₃ octahedra that share corners with three equivalent C(1)Sc₃Al₃ octahedra, corners with three equivalent O(1)Sc₃Al tetrahedra, and edges with nine equivalent C(1)Sc₃Al₃ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Sc(2)³⁺ and one Al(1)³⁺ atom to form distorted OSc₃Al tetrahedra that share corners with three equivalent C(1)Sc₃Al₃ octahedra, corners with nine equivalent O(1)Sc₃Al tetrahedra, and edges with three equivalent O(1)Sc₃Al tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 69°.

BaAl₂B₂O₇ crystallizes in the trigonal R32 space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All Ba(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.779 Å. Al(1)³⁺ is bonded to one O(2)²⁻ and three equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing AlO₄ tetrahedra. The Al(1)-O(2) bond length is 1.691 Å. All Al(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.786 Å. B(1)³⁺ is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All B(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.381 Å. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to one Ba(1)²⁺, one Al(1)³⁺, and one B(1)³⁺ atom. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent Al(1)³⁺ atoms.

LiCaAs is half-Heusler structured and crystallizes in the cubic F̅43m space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms to form LiAs₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Ca(1)As₄ tetrahedra, corners with twelve equivalent Li(1)As₄ tetrahedra, and edges with six equivalent Ca(1)As₄ tetrahedra. All Li(1)-As(1) bond lengths are 2.893 Å. Ca(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms to form CaAs₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Li(1)As₄ tetrahedra, corners with twelve equivalent Ca(1)As₄ tetrahedra, and edges with six equivalent Li(1)As₄ tetrahedra. All Ca(1)-As(1) bond lengths are 2.893 Å. As(1)³⁻ is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to four equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ and four equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ atoms.

MgP₄ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/c space group. Mg(1)²⁺ is bonded to two equivalent P(2)+0.50- and four equivalent P(1)+0.50- atoms to form MgP₆ octahedra that share corners with four equivalent Mg(1)P₆ octahedra, corners with four equivalent P(1)Mg₂P₂ tetrahedra, and corners with ten equivalent P(2)MgP₃ tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 60°. Both Mg(1)-P(2) bond lengths are 2.892 Å. There are two shorter (2.631 Å) and two longer (2.662 Å) Mg(1)-P(1) bond lengths. There are two inequivalent P+0.50- sites. In the first P+0.50- site, P(1)+0.50- is bonded to two equivalent Mg(1)²⁺ and two equivalent P(2)+0.50- atoms to form distorted PMg₂P₂ tetrahedra that share corners with two equivalent Mg(1)P₆ octahedra, corners with six equivalent P(2)MgP₃ tetrahedra, and corners with eight equivalent P(1)Mg₂P₂ tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 69-70°. There is one shorter (2.195 Å) and one longer (2.197 Å) P(1)-P(2) bond length. In the second P+0.50- site, P(2)+0.50- is bonded to one Mg(1)²⁺, one P(2)+0.50-, and two equivalent P(1)+0.50- atoms to form PMgP₃ tetrahedra that share corners with five equivalent Mg(1)P₆ octahedra, corners with three equivalent P(2)MgP₃ tetrahedra, and corners with six equivalent P(1)Mg₂P₂ tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 56-78°. The P(2)-P(2) bond length is 2.270 Å.

NiP₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/c space group. Ni(1)²⁺ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to four equivalent P(1)¹⁻ atoms. There are two shorter (2.207 Å) and two longer (2.208 Å) Ni(1)-P(1) bond lengths. P(1)¹⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Ni(1)²⁺ and two equivalent P(1)¹⁻ atoms to form distorted corner-sharing PNi₂P₂ tetrahedra. There is one shorter (2.239 Å) and one longer (2.244 Å) P(1)-P(1) bond length.

Ca₂NF is Caswellsilverite-like structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/c space group. Ca(1)²⁺ is bonded to three equivalent N(1)³⁻ and three equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing CaN₃F₃ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 0-11°. There are a spread of Ca(1)-N(1) bond distances ranging from 2.371-2.471 Å. There are a spread of Ca(1)-F(1) bond distances ranging from 2.470-2.830 Å. N(1)³⁻ is bonded to six equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ atoms to form NCa₆ octahedra that share corners with two equivalent F(1)Ca₆ octahedra, corners with four equivalent N(1)Ca₆ octahedra, edges with four equivalent N(1)Ca₆ octahedra, and edges with eight equivalent F(1)Ca₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 0-11°. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded to six equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ atoms to form FCa₆ octahedra that share corners with two equivalent N(1)Ca₆ octahedra, corners with four equivalent F(1)Ca₆ octahedra, edges with four equivalent F(1)Ca₆ octahedra, and edges with eight equivalent N(1)Ca₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 0-11°.

ZnTe is Zincblende, Sphalerite structured and crystallizes in the cubic F̅43m space group. Zn(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Te(1)²⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing ZnTe₄ tetrahedra. All Zn(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 2.678 Å. Te(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Zn(1)²⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing TeZn₄ tetrahedra.

RbCuO₂ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmcm space group. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. There are two shorter (2.831 Å) and four longer (3.002 Å) Rb(1)-O(1) bond lengths. Cu(1)³⁺ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. There are two shorter (1.846 Å) and two longer (1.847 Å) Cu(1)-O(1) bond lengths. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Cu(1)³⁺ atoms.

ZnGeP₂ is Chalcopyrite structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅42d space group. Zn(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form ZnP₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Zn(1)P₄ tetrahedra and corners with eight equivalent Ge(1)P₄ tetrahedra. All Zn(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 2.385 Å. Ge(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form GeP₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Ge(1)P₄ tetrahedra and corners with eight equivalent Zn(1)P₄ tetrahedra. All Ge(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 2.358 Å. P(1)³⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Zn(1)²⁺ and two equivalent Ge(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing PZn₂Ge₂ tetrahedra.

(LaO)CuS is Parent of FeAs superconductors structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one CuS sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction and one LaO sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. In the CuS sheet, Cu(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing CuS₄ tetrahedra. All Cu(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.418 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Cu(1)¹⁺ atoms. In the LaO sheet, La(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All La(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.363 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent La(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing OLa₄ tetrahedra.

KLaO₂ is Caswellsilverite structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form KO₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent La(1)O₆ octahedra, edges with six equivalent K(1)O₆ octahedra, and edges with six equivalent La(1)O₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 13°. All K(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.905 Å. La(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form LaO₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent K(1)O₆ octahedra, edges with six equivalent K(1)O₆ octahedra, and edges with six equivalent La(1)O₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 13°. All La(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.467 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to three equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and three equivalent La(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing OK₃La₃ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted.

K₂Zr(BO₃)₂ crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to nine equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. There are six shorter (2.844 Å) and three longer (3.043 Å) K(1)-O(1) bond lengths. Zr(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in an octahedral geometry to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All Zr(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.118 Å. B(1)³⁺ is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All B(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.387 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to three equivalent K(1)¹⁺, one Zr(1)⁴⁺, and one B(1)³⁺ atom.

SiC is Zincblende, Sphalerite structured and crystallizes in the cubic F̅43m space group. Si(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to four equivalent C(1)⁴⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing SiC₄ tetrahedra. All Si(1)-C(1) bond lengths are 1.896 Å. C(1)⁴⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Si(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing CSi₄ tetrahedra.

KCuTe crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃/mmc space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Te(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge, corner, and face-sharing KTe₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 42°. All K(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 3.622 Å. Cu(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent Te(1)²⁻ atoms. All Cu(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 2.582 Å. Te(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to six equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and three equivalent Cu(1)¹⁺ atoms.
